==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nondescript
<hw>non"de*script</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>non-</ets> + L. <ets>descriptus</ets> described.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Not hitherto described;</def> <specif>hence,</specif> <def>of no
recognizable type or class; odd; abnormal; unclassifiable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Dull or uninteresting; undistinguished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nondescript</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nondescript
<hw>Non"de*script</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A thing not yet described;
that of which no account or explanation has been given; something
abnormal, or hardly classifiable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nondevelopment</ent>⟦br⟧
